{
  "stem": "3012.3",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, we knew that we could not stay in the ghetto forever, but we didn't know what's going to happen because of course, the optimism-- the Jewish optimism that whatever happens in the border areas will not affect us because we are only at the Czechoslovakia border, and then that this is a friendly country, Czechoslovakia.",
      "word_count": 56
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "How wrong we were.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Until the 6th of June.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They, they-- I don't now whether it was by written degree-- decree-- or the military or the gendarmes came to tell in the ghetto what was going to happen.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "That I don't remember.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But I know that we had to move out on the 6th of June, 1944.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And as we were walking to-- they said we have to go to a place which they called the gathering point, the concentration camp.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "They didn't use the word concentration camp.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "To camp, probably that's what they said.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And that's where we will stay, which, it turned out, it was a series of stables.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And the certain, certain Jewish men within the forced labor unit were cleaning the streets, and they were whispering to us that the Allied landed in Normandy.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Of course, we were elated, but it was late for us and late for the many millions.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And then we arrived to this stable place, and we had a choice of 'resting,' quote, unquote, on the hay-- on the remnants of the hay just left over by the horses and cows before-- or staying in the open stalls and exposed to the elements.",
      "word_count": 46
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And we chose the latter.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "That was on the 6th, and eventually they brought some more Jews into this camp from the surrounding towns.",
      "word_count": 19
    }
  ],
